            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Three-way matching compares the purchase order, the goods receipt note and the supplier invoice, and payment is released only when all three agree on quantity, rate and value. If the PO covers 100 units at Rs 500, the GRN records 98 units received and the invoice bills 100, the Rs 1,000 gap is queried before posting. It is the standard control against inflated and duplicate vendor payments."
